 YICHANG, Nov. 28 (Xinhua) -- Jinbao Music Instrument Manufacture, founded in 2000, is one of the major musical instrument production bases in the world. Located in Yichang of central China's Hubei Province and along the Yangtze River, various brands of pianos were made in the base and exported to more than 40 countries and regions. The company's production lines of guitar and guzheng, a traditional Chinese musical instrument, will be put into operation at the end of this year, and the annual output of piano here is expected to reach 100,000 units in the future.  Workers make pianos at a workshop of Jinbao Music Instrument Manufacture in Yichang, central China's Hubei Province, Nov. 23, 2021. (Xinhua/Xiao Yijiu)  A worker sets up strings of a piano at a workshop of Jinbao Music Instrument Manufacture in Yichang, central China's Hubei Province, Nov. 23, 2021. (Xinhua/Xiao Yijiu)  A worker tunes a piano at a workshop of Jinbao Music Instrument Manufacture in Yichang, central China's Hubei Province, Nov. 23, 2021. (Xinhua/Xiao Yijiu)  Pianos are displayed at Jinbao Music Instrument Manufacture in Yichang, central China's Hubei Province, Nov. 23, 2021. (Xinhua/Xiao Yijiu)  Produced by Xinhua Global Serviceâ– 